LPR）被摧毁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">过去一天，乌克兰武装部队在顿涅茨克方向损失了多达 210 名士兵，以及 8 辆军事装备，包括一辆坦克、五辆汽车、一门波兰制造的 Krab 自行履带榴弹炮和一门 D-20 榴弹炮.根据俄罗斯外交部的声明，除此之外，还有超过 300 名乌克兰军队在其他作战地区被摧毁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，该部补充说，在朝鲜民主主义人民共和国 Avdiivka 村附近摧毁了两个装有弹药以及乌克兰火箭和火炮武器的仓库。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 10:24:45 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/russian-air-defense-intercepts-12-himars-rockets-storm-shadow-missiles---mod-1110481483.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/russian-air-defense-intercepts-12-himars-rockets-storm-shadow-missiles---mod-1110481483.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>顿涅茨克</category><category>俄罗斯国防部</category><category>高机动火炮火箭系统（HIMARS）</category><category>车牌识别</category><category>俄罗斯</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Israel, Saudi Arabia to Normalize Relations Eventually - Foreign Minister]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110481092" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110480903_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_f814f8ff856bbc28d2bdf21a046a8d79.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110480885" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/israel-saudi-arabia-to-normalize-relations-eventually---foreign-minister-1110481092.html?share-img=1110480885"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Markus Schreiber</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">以色列外交部长伊莱科恩</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Israeli Foreign Minister Eli Cohen  - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="以色列外交部长伊莱·科恩" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110480903_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_42d6c86982e75cb7168871c9cf937366.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110480903_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_b59eae0ed1d0f10a4843410f85a0e7e4.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110480903_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_add1d28c87f6f9680fe84ff63d0ec6ec.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110480903_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_42d6c86982e75cb7168871c9cf937366.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Markus Schreiber </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：以色列外交部长伊莱科恩表示，伊朗与沙特阿拉伯恢复关系不会阻碍以色列与沙特的正常化。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “这不是会不会的问题，而是何时的问题。我们和沙特阿拉伯有相同的利益，”科恩告诉耶路撒冷邮报，评论以色列总理本杰明内塔尼亚胡的话，他一再强调以色列正常化的重要性-沙特关系。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">科恩补充说，利雅得和德黑兰最近恢复关系并不是障碍。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 3 月初，在中国的调解下，伊朗和<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230501/iran-reopens-diplomatic-missions-in-saudi-arabia-1110006977.html" target="_blank">沙特阿拉伯</a>同意恢复外交关系，两国在 2016 年什叶派传教士尼米尔被处决后沙特驻伊朗外交使团遭到袭击后断交。两国外长于4月举行的仪式上签署了恢复外交关系和准备开设外交使团的协议。该协议特别规定恢复两国之间的直航、高级外交官互访和安全合作。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 09:56:22 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/israel-saudi-arabia-to-normalize-relations-eventually---foreign-minister-1110481092.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/israel-saudi-arabia-to-normalize-relations-eventually---foreign-minister-1110481092.html<category>世界</category><category>伊莱科恩</category><category>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡</category><category>沙特阿拉伯</category><category>以色列</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[G7 Countries to Create Platform to Counter Economic Coercion]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110480375" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_08fcc47d6a64c8f66958df187c328bb4.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110255112" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-img=1110255112"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / KAZUHIRO NOGI</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 5 月 10 日，在新泻县新泻火车站，人们走下展示即将举行的 G7 财长和中央银行行长会议标志的楼梯</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="People walk down stairs displaying the logo of the upcoming G7 Finance Ministers and Central Bank Governors' Meeting at Niigata railway station in Niigata on May 10, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2023 年 5 月 10 日，在新泻县新泻火车站，人们走下楼梯，展示即将举行的 G7 财长和中央银行行长会议的标志" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_6f58a11e0d32f65681aeec399ae3f7e2.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_b353c6efaa05086f406bc70c2f931054.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_d2ec5b33945a0ee749e833bdf6feb137.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_6f58a11e0d32f65681aeec399ae3f7e2.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / KAZUHIRO NOGI </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据广岛（人造卫星）网报道：七国集团（G7）国家领导人发表了关于经济弹性和经济安全的声明，表达了他们对经济胁迫事件“令人不安的上升”的担忧，并承诺采取行动打击此类做法周六。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">声明中写道：“世界遇到了令人不安的经济胁迫事件增加，这些事件试图利用经济脆弱性和依赖性，破坏<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220715/on-the-bastille-day-anniversary-another-g7-member-resigns-1097326641.html" target="_blank">七国集团成员</a>以及世界各地合作伙伴的国内外政策和立场。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他们还承诺共同努力，确保将经济依赖武器化的企图“失败并面临后果”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “认识到包括 WTO [世界贸易组织]在内的现有共同努力的重要性，我们将通过启动经济胁迫协调平台来加强合作，以加强我们对经济胁迫的集体评估、准备、威慑和反应，并进一步促进与七国集团以外的合作伙伴，”声明中写道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110480375" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-block=1110480378" data-title="&quot;Recognizing the importance of existing joint efforts including at the WTO [World Trade Organization], we will enhance collaboration by launching the Coordination Platform on Economic Coercion to increase our collective assessment, preparedness, deterrence and response to economic coercion, and further promote cooperation with partners beyond the G7,&quot; the statement read. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在该平台内，七国集团国家将根据各自的法律制度，利用预警和快速信息共享，定期相互磋商，共同评估形势，探索协调应对措施，遏制并在适当情况下反制经济胁迫。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据他们的联合公报，七国集团领导人及其合作伙伴承诺发起所谓的《广岛全球粮食安全弹性行动声明》，以满足当前和未来的粮食需求。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">声明中写道：“我们承诺按照所附的‘有弹性的全球粮食安全广岛行动声明’所述，与伙伴国家采取具体步骤，并呼吁在国际社会开展更广泛的合作。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110480375" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-block=1110480381" data-title="&quot;We commit to taking concrete steps with partner countries as outlined in the annexed 'Hiroshima Action Statement for Resilient Global Food Security,' and call for broader cooperation in the international community,&quot; the statement read."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">七国集团领导人反对在世界任何地方以武力单方面改变领土地位的任何企图，并寻求加强核不扩散努力，以实现无核武器世界的最终目标。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">声明中写道：“我们将通过强烈反对在世界任何地方通过武力或胁迫改变和平建立的领土地位的任何单方面企图，并重申禁止以武力获取领土，来捍卫国际原则和共同价值观。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110480375" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-block=1110480383" data-title="&quot;We will champion international principles and shared values by strongly opposing any unilateral attempts to change the peacefully established status of territories by force or coercion anywhere in the world and reaffirming that the acquisition of territory by force is prohibited,&quot; the statement read."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">领导人还表示，他们正在采取具体步骤“加强裁军和防扩散努力，以实现一个没有核武器的世界和所有人的安全都不会受到削弱的最终目标”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他们还重申致力于普遍加入、有效实施和加强《禁止生物和毒素武器公约》以及《 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230301/chemical-weapons-provocation-brewing-in-ukraine-anti-war-movement-grows-bakhmut-encirclement-near-1107886012.html" target="_blank">禁止化学武器</a>公约》。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据公报，七国集团领导人仍准备与中国建立建设性和稳定的关系，并呼吁北京与该集团接触。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们随时准备与中国建立建设性和稳定的关系，认识到与中国坦诚接触并直接向中国表达关切的重要性，”该组织表示，并补充说“有必要”与北京进行沟通。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110480375" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-block=1110480388" data-title="&quot;We stand prepared to build constructive and stable relations with China, recognizing the importance of engaging candidly with and expressing our concerns directly to China,&quot; the group said, adding that &quot;it was necessary&quot; to communicate with Beijing."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">声明称<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/japanese-indonesian-leaders-discuss-cooperation-at-g7-summit--1110476978.html" target="_blank">，七国集团领导人</a>在台湾问题上的立场没有改变，包括一个中国政策。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">声明说：“我们重申台海和平与稳定对国际社会的安全与繁荣不可或缺的重要性……我们呼吁和平解决两岸问题。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110480375" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html?share-block=1110480390" data-title="&quot;We reaffirm the importance of peace and stability across the Taiwan Strait as indispensable to security and prosperity in the international community… We call for a peaceful resolution of cross-Strait issues,&quot; the statement said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该组织还反对北京在南海的军事活动。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “中国在南海扩大海洋主张没有法律依据，我们反对中国在该地区的军事化活动，”它说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> G7 峰会将于 5 月 19 日至 21 日在广岛举行，重点讨论乌克兰冲突、经济安全、绿色投资和印太地区的发展。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">印度、澳大利亚、巴西、韩国、越南、印度尼西亚、科摩罗、库克群岛等国领导人以及联合国、世界银行、和世界卫生组织。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 09:04:51 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/g7-countries-to-create-platform-to-counter-economic-coercion-1110480375.html<category>世界</category><category>G7</category><category>世界贸易组织 (WTO)</category><category>广岛</category><category>化学武器公约</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Huge Weight of New York's Skyscrapers May Cause City to Collapse & Sink, Study Warns]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110478453" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110477788_0:0:3070:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_a87ddf56df41548c0502d69da65206ae.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110477770" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html?share-img=1110477770"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Julia Nikhinson</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">布鲁克林大桥越过布鲁克林大桥公园的旋转木马，横跨东河，背景是纽约天际线。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="The Brooklyn Bridge passes over the carousel at Brooklyn Bridge Park and spans the East River with the New York skyline in the background. - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="布鲁克林大桥越过布鲁克林大桥公园的旋转木马，横跨东河，背景是纽约天际线。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110477788_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_52fdaeba9e18fa8bcc64ca1e373613d7.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110477788_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_43798405221ae81092ff6eb26034495a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110477788_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_e77c71e35770a5dd4e08af6f0dc145e8.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110477788_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_52fdaeba9e18fa8bcc64ca1e373613d7.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Julia Nikhinson </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">斯韦特兰娜·埃基缅科</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_svetlana_ekimenko/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:s.ekimenko@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">去年进行的一项研究调查了不同国家的大约 99 个沿海城市，发现“沉降”或下沉在未来可能是比大肆宣传的与气候相关的海平面上升更大的威胁，居民可能面临洪水比预期的要早。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据最近一项研究的可怕预测，纽约可能会成为一个巨大的水坑。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这座大都市也被称为大苹果，拥有引人注目的天际线，拥有一系列世界上最高的建筑，例如世界贸易中心一号大楼或中央公园大厦，但它是所有这些建筑的总重量可能导致城市崩溃的巨人。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据罗德岛大学海洋学家和美国地质调查局科学家的研究，这座地势低洼的城市正<strong>以每年 1-2 毫米的速度下沉</strong>。他们的发现发表在<a href="https://agupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1029/2022EF003465" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">《地球的未来》</a>杂志上。此外，还补充说“某些地区”，例如曼哈顿下城、布鲁克林和皇后区，“下沉速度要快得多”。这是用来描述下沉的技术术语。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">作为研究的一部分，研究人员计算了纽约市建筑物及其内部物品的重量，得出的重量高达 7640 亿公斤。之后，他们将城市分成100平方米的正方形，并模拟了这些建筑物施加的“向下压力”。该团队考虑了这些地区的地质和土壤条件，例如基岩、沙子、淤泥和粘土湖沉积物。海拔变化是使用卫星数据测量的。结果相当惊人。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110478453" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110478021_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_8fddb1936a709d92ce92404449464fb9.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110478003" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html?share-img=1110478003"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Julia Nikhinson</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2022 年 11 月 14 日，星期一，纽约，帝国大厦在黄昏时分发出蓝光。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="The Empire State Building glows blue during dusk, Monday, Nov. 14, 2022, in New York.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2022 年 11 月 14 日星期一，纽约，帝国大厦在黄昏时分发出蓝光。" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110478021_0:0:3072:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_c7223d2c07ea465c4ed39519b0e34d80.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221280%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1280" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110478021_0:0:3072:2048_640x0_80_0_0_e00161462c52cf544d60156ca6d5a471.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110478021_0:0:3072:2048_1280x0_80_0_0_49eb4ef9c73a61a0eff482dca08d65f4.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/14/1110478021_0:0:3072:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_c7223d2c07ea465c4ed39519b0e34d80.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet=""> 2022 年 11 月 14 日星期一，纽约，帝国大厦在黄昏时分发出蓝光。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Julia Nikhinson </div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “构造和人为沉降、海平面上升和飓风强度增加的结合意味着沿海和沿河地区的问题正在加速……建筑物地基反复暴露在盐水中会腐蚀钢筋和化学削弱混凝土，导致结构弱化， ”作者强调。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110478453" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html?share-block=1110478640" data-title="&amp;quot;The combination of tectonic and anthropogenic subsidence, sea level rise, and increasing hurricane intensity imply an accelerating problem along coastal and riverfront areas... Repeated exposure of building foundations to salt water can corrode reinforcing steel and chemically weaken concrete, causing structural weakening,” the authors highlighted."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管许多摩天大楼耸立的基岩不易下沉，但粘土和人造填料等基材却很容易下沉。该研究的目的是提醒人们注意纽约极易受到<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220216/coastal-america-to-face-fivefold-increase-in-destructive-floods-by-2050-report-warns-1093071762.html" target="_blank">未来洪水的</a>影响这一事实。研究表明，曼哈顿下城的大部分地区海拔不超过 1 至 2 米。该团队提到了 2012 年飓风桑迪和 2021 年飓风艾达造成的破坏，并警告说纽约市“在未来暴露于沿海洪水的资产方面”位居世界第三。然而，据科学家称，“飓风桑迪后扩大的洪水风险区的 67,400 座建筑物中有 90% 并未按照洪泛区标准建造。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “纽约面临洪水灾害的重大挑战；海平面上升的威胁比北美大西洋沿岸的全球平均水平高 3 到 4 倍……纽约市 840 万高度集中的人口面临不同程度的洪水灾害，”地质学家汤姆·帕森斯 (Tom Parsons)美国地质调查局 (USGS) 和他在罗德岛大学的同事说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110478453" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html?share-block=1110478642" data-title="“New York faces significant challenges from flood hazard; the threat of sea level rise is 3 to 4 times higher than the global average along the Atlantic coast of North America … A deeply concentrated population of 8.4 million people faces varying degrees of hazard from inundation in New York City,” geologist Tom Parsons of the United States Geological Survey (USGS) and his colleagues at the University of Rhode Island said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该团队估计，未来在“沿海、河流或湖滨环境”建造的每一栋高层建筑都可能“增加未来的洪水风险”。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 08:01:04 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/huge-weight-of-new-yorks-skyscrapers-may-cause-it-to-collapse--sink-study-warns--1110478453.html<category>超越政治</category><category>我们</category><category>纽约市</category><category>摩天大楼</category><category>洪水</category><category>飓风艾达</category><category>罗德岛大学</category><category>美国地质调查局 (USGS)</category><category>曼哈顿</category><category>纽约</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hiroshima Bombing Survivor Speaks Against Zelensky's Arrival]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110479077" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/06/1080082093_0:0:3115:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_12fe1d5c25024b83d80cea51ba28366a.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1080082091" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/hiroshima-bombing-survivor-speaks-against-zelenskys-arrival-1110479077.html?share-img=1080082091"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">广岛</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Hiroshima - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="广岛" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/06/1080082093_0:148:3115:1900_1920x0_80_0_0_9ea83c136fdd1fd838dc3dc3823f24e4.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/06/1080082093_0:148:3115:1900_640x0_80_0_0_076abb387574660185381657362e1c83.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/06/1080082093_0:148:3115:1900_1280x0_80_0_0_a5ff6eba5e3eece7705eebcae8baee5c.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/06/1080082093_0:148:3115:1900_1920x0_80_0_0_9ea83c136fdd1fd838dc3dc3823f24e4.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> ©人造卫星</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">星期六，乌克兰总统沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基乘坐法国政府专机抵达日本广岛机场，七国集团领导人峰会正在那里举行。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">广岛原子弹爆炸幸存者协会主席、广岛原子弹爆炸幸存者佐久间邦彦在新闻发布会上表示，在当前的政治气候下，他无法接受泽伦斯基的访问。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “将来他可以来，看看广岛，了解原子弹爆炸事件。但在目前的政治条件下，政治讨价还价的动机非常强烈，在这种情况下访问广岛，我不知道是不是为你，但我不能同意，”佐久间说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110479077" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/hiroshima-bombing-survivor-speaks-against-zelenskys-arrival-1110479077.html?share-block=1110479079" data-title="&amp;quot;In the future he could come, see Hiroshima, learn about the bombing. But in the present political conditions, the motive of political bargaining is very strong in coming to Hiroshima, and in these conditions with visiting Hiroshima, I don&amp;#x27;t know as for you, but I can&amp;#x27;t agree,&amp;quot; Sakuma said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2023年，七国集团轮值主席国移交给日本。 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/hiroshima-g7-summit-just-photo-op-for-bidens-confrontation-with-china-1110458775.html" target="_blank">G7 峰会</a>将于 5 月 19 日至 21 日在广岛举行，重点讨论乌克兰冲突、经济安全、绿色投资和印太地区的发展。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">印度、澳大利亚、巴西、韩国、越南、印度尼西亚、科摩罗、库克群岛等国领导人以及联合国、世界银行、和世界卫生组织。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 07:55:36 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/hiroshima-bombing-survivor-speaks-against-zelenskys-arrival-1110479077.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/hiroshima-bombing-survivor-speaks-against-zelenskys-arrival-1110479077.html<category>世界</category><category>沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基</category><category>广岛</category><category>日本</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>G7峰会</category></item></channel></rss>